<br>
One key is after the first run through kill the Yeti's as they spawn - don't wait until all have respawned.  Sometimes other players come through looking for a quick kill or two.  If there's nothing for them to kill, they usually leave quickly.  Once or twice I got squeezed into camping one room, but for the most part I had the whole cavern to myself for hours on end.  These caves are a pretty well kept secret though.  One night there were 80+ players in dreadlands, no one in Yeti Caves except for me.  If the caves are crowded during peak hours on your server, then set the alarm clock for 2 in the morning and do it then - you don't need to be in top form mentally to run through the spawns. <br>
<br>
I started getting a little more than two blues per 20 min or so spawn at 40 and at 43 got a little less than that.  Was tempted to stay here awhile even at 44 because I still got 1.5 blues for all seven Yetis but finally had to leave because I was sick of Yetis.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ukraygus.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kraygus</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#333333>(10/18/02 5:37:12 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerlevels3943.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=6.topic&index=35>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_sunglasses.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Yetis, Yes; Caves, No</span><hr size=1> Another alternative that I used from 39-44 was to hunt outside of the Yeti Caves (#7 on the EQ Atlas map), near position neg160,pos3400. This will put you on top of a mountain, overlooking the building housing the entrance to the #7 caves.<br>
<br>
Just to the north of this mountain is a valley with a very busy east-west highway of Drolvags, Giants, Yetis, Spiders, and Cockatrices. From 39-42 these were all in the dark blue range. At level 43, maybe 1/3 of these started to change to light blue.<br>
<br>
The strategy I used was to create a fire pet (focused and fully equiped), and park him at the top of this hill - right in the middle of the plateau. By using your new ring of flight (always keep lev on yourself) you can easily run between mountain ranges and use your level 8 bolt spell to pull NPCs back to your pet. If you cast from high on a hill, you don't even need SOW to outrun the NPCs. You'll be running in essentially a straight line (thanks to lev) back to your hill, while the NPCs have to run down the mountain, then back up to your hill (a greater distance). Always fight on top of this hill and you'll never pick up any adds.<br>
<br>
If you get drolvags, Yetis, or cockatrices, your pet can ususally solo them without your help. Ping them with your bolt (40 mana) pull them to your hill and attack them with your pet. Sit down (always in the middle of the plateau so you don't aggro any nearby wanders) and med. I found doing this I could hunt nearly constantly, and actually *gain* mana. (39 Fire pets regen very fast, and kill NPCs fast too!). Occassionally, I would throw in an extra DD just to help Jobobar along, and sometimes a heal if he needed it. These NPCs would drop occasional gems and misc other items, along with 0-4pp.<br>
<br>
Occasionally you'll hit an NPC at the outer limit of the bolt range, which is too far for the NPC to figure out who hit it. When this happens it will starting running away. (The yetis look hillarious when this happens.) You'll want to keep an eye out for this and run after them until you get close enough for them to &quot;see&quot; you. Having levitate on will help you catch up to them quickly, if you're starting at a higher altitude. Letting them go can have unpredictable results. Most of the time they just wander away never to be seen again. However, they're spreading your name onto the hate list of all the other NPCs that they come in contact with and you may end up getting more attention than you want later on.<br>
<br>
Giants are a lot of fun and drop items including tunics which sell for 60pp at vendors. Pull them using the same technique. The level 8 bolt only does 50 dam, so your pet easily gets the aggro off you. After your pet has dropped the Giant down a bubble, cast rain of lava on him and then heal your pet. If you're lucky the fight will be over. If you get resists, then you may need to add another 39 bolt (cinder). <br>
<br>
One other thing to note - normally the NPCs &quot;flee&quot; when they get down to 1 bub of HP. This gives Jobobar &quot;free&quot; time to finish the NPC off and regen at the same time. However, if Jobobar is down below 2 bubs himself, the NPCs (especially giants) will stick it out to the end. If the NPC is down to 1 bub and hasn't started to flee, stand up and attack it. Looking at your full health bar will cause the NPC to flee and Jobobar and wrap things up.<br>
<br>
In general, I avoided the spiders. Because they are casters, I would have to help my pet with additional heals and DDs, making them less efficient XP producers.<br>
<br>
Using this approach, I would get 1-1.25 yellow bubs of XP per hour, and averaged around 100pp per hour too (this would easily fund KEI, which would improve your hunting rate considerably - dang, why didn't I do that?). I found the variety of NPCs and the wide open spaces to be more interesting than just camping the caves. Good luck! <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ukraygus.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kraygus</A> at: 10/18/02 5:44:29 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uravian.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ravian</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 63<br> <font color=#333333>(10/19/02 8:59:58 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerlevels3943.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=6.topic&index=36>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_sunglasses.gif" align=absmiddle>  oh yeah</span><hr size=1> Good place to fight I am there currently.  Dont tell anyone on Xegony for about 3 more days <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uravian.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ravian</A> at: 10/19/02 9:00:55 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uravian.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ravian</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 65<br> <font color=#333333>(10/21/02 1:16:08 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerlevels3943.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=6.topic&index=37>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_sunglasses.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: oh yeah</span><hr size=1> Ok I am out of there now I have about 2 hours left until ding 44 on the yetis.  I am moving on even though they are still giving me decent XP I want to get used to my next zone with my new pets at 44.<br>
<br>
I just wanted to post my experience here from lvl 38 on up.  I cam here at 38 so I could test it out and see how it was and I also could not stand DSP anymore.  I would be happy if I never saw a Zelniak or a Blood Starved Wolf Again.  First thing I did knowing that I did not have enough real fire power for this zone I made sure I got KEI before going.<br>
<br>
Well my only death came from the very first time I zoned into DL.  I started out by binding In the Nexus for easy sell and acquiring KEI.  It is a lot easier to get a port to DL from the nexus than to get a port from DL to nexus.  I bound in nexus got KEI and ported to DL.  I ran along the large snow covered side of the mountain just to the side of the spires until I came to the mouth of a small cave. <br>
<br>
This cave led to the other side of DL.  Upon entering the other side of DL I invised up and when I could I cast levitate.  This is where I died I let invis drop and didnt notice I got stuck by two spiders who cast root and DoT which killed me.  Stay away from the two spiders they hunt in pairs and hit hard.  When I got lev it made it a lot easier to travel to the yeti cave. <br>
<br>
Exiting the cave I took a right and ran along the snowy mountain side once agin until I saw to Stone pillars marking the ent. of the yeti cave.  The fist time in the yeti cave I was quite nervous but I soon got over that and it became very simple.  I summoned my earth pet so that I could chain them if I needed.  At this level I found that it was pretty easy to do but was not all that mana effective. <br>
<br>
I did it anyway and when the yeti was at about 50 health I blazed him up.  I would pull with malise.  and even though they are practically stacked on top of each other they all pull as singles with spells or pet fighting them in there spot.  I would pull with malise to make sure jobbers root would stick and my nukes would hit.  when you hit 40 or so malise is rarely needed. <br>
<br>
When I dinged 39 I broke out the new and improved pets.  I suited pet up with a full suit of plate and two swords I BO2'd him and expediance and DS some of the time.  You could tell a big diffference in downtime with BO2 and Equipment rather than without it.  I kept KEI up always which allowed for quick leveling.  I made more than enough money while camping this spawn to make up for the 50pp in Nexus for KEI and 35 for port back to DL.  <br>
<br>
After hiting 39 it was very easy to hold all 7 spawns so I got bored and decided to pull more from outside the Cave.  I found that the best bang for the buck were the Davalargs or whatever they are called.  There seems to tons of them around and they almost all drop 4pp at least some times more and they seem to drop gems that sell for 10pp a lot more often.  They helped me earn money and good exp while waiting for the repop.  They hit harder on the pet so you will want to burn them down quicker but they have not as many hit points as the yetis so they go down quicker.  <br>
<br>
I would also take down the giants when they were in bolt distance.  I would sit in the mouth of the cave and cast a bolt spell when there was a mob in range.  That way I stayed out of aggro of all other mobs this kept adds down to 0 only with the ocasional spider did I get any adds.  I did kill giants they drop gems 5g-5pp and axes that sell for about 2pp each and one out of about 50 droped a tunic that sold for 50pp to the vendor.  They were a better sense of accomplishment more than anything and were more fun but very mana entensive not nearly as exp effective as the davalargs. <br>
<br>
I would pull outside for about 5-15 minutes as long as there were mobs to pull and then I would go back in and fight more yetis. This made for almost non stop fighitng.  Pets health was the only real limiting factor and occasionally a little medding for KEI if you had a horsey you would never need to stop except for pet to regain.  I wouldnt bother with pet healing because they regain hp so fast when sitting.  <br>
<br>
I flew through lvls 39-44 here about twice as fast as 34-39 so live it up this place was great have fun it is non stop fighting.  I grouped for a little while one night and got about 15% exp in about the time I would have gotten 2.5 yellows solo.  So be glad your a Mage.  Mage POWAH!!!!  Oh yeah and get fired up 44 pets are BAD ACE! <p><img src=http://www.legionoffyre.net/disappearing%20flame.gif><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=425856><b>Ravian Varior</b></a><img src=http://www.legionoffyre.net/disappearing%20flame.gif><br><a href=http://www.legionoffyre.net><b>----{}Legion of Fyer{}---</b></a><br><b>---LVL 44 Erudite Mage---</b><br><a href=http://pub17.ezboard.com/bxegony >----------Xegony----------</a>
